     2→/**************************************************************************************************
     3→ *  PulseSphere SocialOps – System Monitoring
     4→ *  ------------------------------------------------------------
     5→ *  File:        src/module_58.ts
     6→ *  Responsibility:
     7→ *      • Observe real-time social-interaction metrics coming from Kafka.
     8→ *      • Dynamically decide which backup strategy (full | incremental) should run next.
     9→ *      • Dispatch backup commands and handle execution lifecycle.
    10→ *      • Expose a minimal API that other micro-services can use to trigger/observe backups.
    11→ *
    12→ *  Architectural Patterns Demonstrated:
    13→ *      • Observer                         – Configuration hot-reload & metric listeners.
    14→ *      • Strategy                         – Full vs Incremental backup decision making.
    15→ *      • Command                          – Encapsulating backup instructions.
    16→ *      • Chain-of-Responsibility          – Recovery pipeline.
    17→ *
    18→ *  NOTE:
    19→ *      This module purposefully hides IO details (S3, pg_dump, etc.) behind strategy & command
    20→ *      abstractions so the rest of the codebase can stay agnostic.
    21→ **************************************************************************************************/
    22→
    23→// ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    24→// Imports
